---
import ContactForm from '@components/ContactForm.astro'
import Grid from '@components/Grid.astro'
import Layout from '@layouts/Layout.astro'
import CaseStudySectionText from '@components/case-studies/case-study/CaseStudySectionText.astro'
import CaseStudyResults from '@components/case-studies/case-study/CaseStudyResults.astro'
import CaseStudyHeader from '@components/case-studies/case-study/CaseStudyHeader.astro'
import CaseStudyToggleButton from '@components/case-studies/case-study/CaseStudyToggleButton.astro'
import CaseStudyMetaData from '@components/case-studies/case-study/CaseStudyMetaData.astro'
import CaseStudyShout from '@components/case-studies/case-study/CaseStudyShout.astro'
import CaseStudyNav from '@components/case-studies/case-study/CaseStudyNav.astro'
import CaseStudyImages from '@components/case-studies/case-study/CaseStudyImages.astro'

import hero from '@assets/case-studies/miele/hero.webp'
import squareOne from '@assets/case-studies/miele/squareOne.svg'
import squareTwo from '@assets/case-studies/miele/squareTwo.webp'
import wideOne from '@assets/case-studies/miele/wideOne.webp'
import wideTwo from '@assets/case-studies/miele/wideTwo.webp'
---

<Layout
  title="Miele Case Study"
  description="Digital consulting and strategy for Miele Australia, the local arm of the German premium appliance manufacturer, in the domestic and commercial appliances sector. Pixel Agency mapped Miele Australia's full technology landscape ahead of the global SAP S/4HANA transition, building the business case for a market-specific implementation now serving as a benchmark for similar Miele markets."
  published={false}
>
  <article id="case-study-page">
    <CaseStudyHeader>
      <span slot="title">Miele Australia</span>
      <span slot="industry">Home Appliances</span>
      <span slot="services">Consulting</span>
      <span slot="duration">2 months</span>
    </CaseStudyHeader>

    <CaseStudyToggleButton />

    <!-- Single shell: all images + summary (left pane) / all case study text (right pane) -->
    <section class="pb-12 lg:pb-18">
      <Grid>
        <div id="case-study-shell" class="case-study-shell col-span-full">
          <div class="case-study-left-pane min-w-0 overflow-hidden">
            <CaseStudyImages
              heroImage={{ src: hero }}
              summary="How Pixel Agency helped Miele Australia document its full technology and data landscape ahead of a global SAP S/4HANA rollout, making the case for a market-specific implementation now serving as the benchmark for similar Miele markets."
              squareImages={[{ src: squareOne }, { src: squareTwo }]}
              wideImages={[{ src: wideOne }, { src: wideTwo }]}
            />
          </div>

          <div class="case-study-right-pane min-w-0">
            <CaseStudyShout>
              Mapped Miele Australia's full technology landscape ahead of the global SAP S/4HANA transition, winning
              approval for a market-specific implementation now benchmarking similar Miele markets.
            </CaseStudyShout>

            <CaseStudySectionText title="The client" noTopMargin={true}>
              <p class="">
                Miele Australia is the local arm of Miele, the German manufacturer known for premium white goods and
                kitchen equipment built to last decades. Unusually within the global Miele network, the Australian
                business runs both a B2C and a B2B model, where the vast majority of Miele markets are B2B only. That
                dual operating model means Miele Australia carries a much larger customer base, more sensitive customer
                data, and more integrated systems than the rest of the group.
              </p>
            </CaseStudySectionText>

            <CaseStudySectionText title="The problem">
              <p>
                Miele globally was moving from a patchwork of legacy ERPs to SAP S/4HANA, and Miele Australia was one of
                the very first markets in the world to make the transition. Global was working from a single blueprint
                built around the typical Miele B2B market, which looked nothing like the Australian reality. Miele
                Australia's reporting stack runs the business day-to-day, and applying the global blueprint as-is would
                have meant key reports could no longer be produced, with operations grinding to a halt as a result. With
                two other Miele markets watching Australia as the benchmark for their own transitions, the stakes
                weren't just local.
              </p>
            </CaseStudySectionText>

            <CaseStudySectionText title="The approach">
              <p>
                Pixel was brought in as a partner alongside another consultancy to advise Miele Australia on how to
                actually carry out the transition. The first thing that became clear was sobering: between the age of
                the systems and the number of moving parts, no one inside the business had a complete technical picture.
                Before we could advise on anything, we had to build that picture from the ground up. We worked across
                the full OSI model, mapping the entire network, data centres, systems, integrations, data warehouses,
                printers, and reports, identifying what was in active use, what had been orphaned, what needed patching,
                and who owned each piece.
              </p>
            </CaseStudySectionText>

            <CaseStudySectionText title="The solution">
              <p>
                Out of that mapping came a documented understanding of how Miele Australia actually runs, and where the
                gaps would open up if the global SAP S/4HANA blueprint were applied without adaptation. We mapped each
                existing system to its SAP equivalent, called out where market-specific customisation would be required,
                and built the case Miele global needed to see. Along the way, we identified a long-standing data
                fragmentation issue: customer information lived across multiple CRMs and marketing tools that didn't
                cleanly talk to the source of truth, which had been quietly causing problems like opted-out customers
                still receiving marketing. We provided a solution plan to resolve it as part of the broader transition.
              </p>
            </CaseStudySectionText>

            <CaseStudySectionText title="The results">
              <p>
                Phase one delivered the strategic outcome that mattered most: Miele Australia made the case that a
                one-size-fits-all SAP rollout wouldn't work for its market, and global agreed.
              </p>
              <CaseStudyResults
                results={[
                  {
                    title: 'Complete documentation',
                    description: "of Miele Australia's technology and data landscape",
                    backgroundColour: 'pixel-solar'
                  },
                  {
                    title: 'A full mapping',
                    description: 'of legacy systems to SAP S/4HANA, with gaps identified',
                    backgroundColour: 'pixel-celestial'
                  },
                  {
                    title: 'A solution plan',
                    description:
                      'to consolidate fragmented customer data and stop opted-out customers receiving marketing material',
                    backgroundColour: 'pixel-rosy'
                  },
                  {
                    title: 'Accepted case by Miele global',
                    description: 'opening the door to market-specific customisation',
                    backgroundColour: 'pixel-teal'
                  },
                  {
                    title: 'A framework`',
                    description: 'informing the two other Miele markets with similar B2C/B2B operating models',
                    backgroundColour: 'pixel-teal'
                  },
                  {
                    title: 'Signed off implementation plan',
                    description: 'awaiting budget for the build phase',
                    backgroundColour: 'pixel-teal'
                  }
                ]}
              />

              <div class="mt-6 lg:mt-12"></div>

              <CaseStudyShout>
                Before you can move a business to a new platform, you have to know what you're actually moving.
              </CaseStudyShout>
            </CaseStudySectionText>

            <CaseStudyMetaData
              client={{ name: 'Miele', url: 'https://www.miele.com.au/' }}
              industry={['Home Appliances']}
              serviceNames={['Consulting']}
            />
          </div>
        </div>
      </Grid>
    </section>

    {/* Navigation section */}
    <CaseStudyNav
      previousCaseStudy={{ name: 'Previous case study', slug: 'previous-case-study' }}
      nextCaseStudy={{ name: 'Next case study', slug: 'next-case-study' }}
    />

    <ContactForm title="Discuss a similar challenge" displayDescription={false} />
  </article>

  <style>
    #case-study-page {
      --case-study-border: color-mix(in oklab, var(--color-black) 8%, transparent);
      --case-study-placeholder: var(--color-pixel-placeholder-grey);
    }

    @media (max-width: 1023px) {
      .case-study-shell {
        display: flex;
        gap: 0;
        overflow: clip;
      }

      .case-study-left-pane {
        flex: 0 0 auto;
        width: 100%;
        max-height: 5000px;
        opacity: 1;
        transform: translateX(0);
        transition:
          width 420ms cubic-bezier(0.22, 1, 0.36, 1),
          max-height 420ms cubic-bezier(0.22, 1, 0.36, 1),
          opacity 240ms ease,
          transform 420ms cubic-bezier(0.22, 1, 0.36, 1);
        will-change: width, max-height, opacity, transform;
      }

      #case-study-page[data-panel-state='open'] .case-study-left-pane {
        width: 0;
        max-height: 0;
        opacity: 0;
        transform: translateX(-2rem);
        pointer-events: none;
      }

      .case-study-right-pane {
        flex: 0 0 auto;
        width: 0;
        max-height: 0;
        opacity: 0;
        overflow: clip;
        transform: translateX(2rem);
        transition:
          width 420ms cubic-bezier(0.22, 1, 0.36, 1),
          max-height 420ms cubic-bezier(0.22, 1, 0.36, 1),
          opacity 260ms ease,
          transform 420ms cubic-bezier(0.22, 1, 0.36, 1);
        will-change: width, max-height, opacity, transform;
      }

      #case-study-page[data-panel-state='open'] .case-study-right-pane {
        width: 100%;
        max-height: 5000px;
        opacity: 1;
        transform: translateX(0);
        pointer-events: auto;
      }
    }

    @media (min-width: 1024px) {
      .case-study-shell {
        display: flex;
        gap: 0;
        transition: gap 420ms cubic-bezier(0.22, 1, 0.36, 1);
      }

      #case-study-page[data-panel-state='open'] .case-study-shell {
        gap: 1.25rem;
      }

      .case-study-left-pane,
      .case-study-right-pane {
        flex: 0 0 auto;
        transition:
          width 420ms cubic-bezier(0.22, 1, 0.36, 1),
          max-height 420ms cubic-bezier(0.22, 1, 0.36, 1),
          opacity 260ms ease,
          transform 420ms cubic-bezier(0.22, 1, 0.36, 1);
        will-change: width, max-height, opacity, transform;
      }

      .case-study-left-pane {
        width: 100%;
        max-height: 5000px;
      }

      .case-study-right-pane {
        width: 0;
        max-height: 0;
        opacity: 0;
        transform: translateX(2rem);
        overflow: clip;
        pointer-events: none;
      }

      #case-study-page[data-panel-state='open'] .case-study-left-pane {
        width: calc(50% - 0.625rem);
      }

      #case-study-page[data-panel-state='open'] .case-study-right-pane {
        width: calc(50% - 0.625rem);
        max-height: 5000px;
        opacity: 1;
        transform: translateX(0);
        pointer-events: auto;
      }
    }

    @media (prefers-reduced-motion: reduce) {
      .case-study-shell,
      .case-study-left-pane,
      .case-study-right-pane {
        transition: none;
      }
    }
  </style>

  <script>
    function initCaseStudyPage() {
      const page = document.getElementById('case-study-page')
      const toggle = document.getElementById('case-study-toggle')
      if (!(page instanceof HTMLElement) || !(toggle instanceof HTMLButtonElement)) return
      const pageElement = page
      const toggleButton = toggle

      const mobileMedia = window.matchMedia('(max-width: 1023px)')

      function setToggleTextColor() {
        const accent = getComputedStyle(document.documentElement).getPropertyValue('--accent-bgc').trim()
        const match = accent.match(/(\d+)\s*,\s*(\d+)\s*,\s*(\d+)/)
        if (!match) return

        let red = parseInt(match[1], 10) / 255
        let green = parseInt(match[2], 10) / 255
        let blue = parseInt(match[3], 10) / 255

        red = red <= 0.03928 ? red / 12.92 : Math.pow((red + 0.055) / 1.055, 2.4)
        green = green <= 0.03928 ? green / 12.92 : Math.pow((green + 0.055) / 1.055, 2.4)
        blue = blue <= 0.03928 ? blue / 12.92 : Math.pow((blue + 0.055) / 1.055, 2.4)

        const luminance = 0.2126 * red + 0.7152 * green + 0.0722 * blue
        document.documentElement.style.setProperty('--case-study-toggle-text', luminance > 0.4 ? '#000' : '#fff')
      }

      function getDefaultState() {
        return 'closed'
      }

      if (!pageElement.dataset.panelState) {
        pageElement.dataset.panelState = getDefaultState()
      }

      function syncA11y() {
        const isOpen = pageElement.dataset.panelState === 'open'
        toggleButton.setAttribute('aria-expanded', String(isOpen))
      }

      setToggleTextColor()
      syncA11y()

      toggleButton.addEventListener('click', () => {
        pageElement.dataset.panelState = pageElement.dataset.panelState === 'open' ? 'closed' : 'open'
        syncA11y()
      })
    }

    initCaseStudyPage()
    document.addEventListener('astro:after-swap', initCaseStudyPage)
  </script>
</Layout>
